      "title": "Neural circuits encode prior knowledge of temporal statistics",
      "content": "<p>Nature Neuroscience, Published online: 07 April 2026; <a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41593-026-02255-7\">doi:10.1038/s41593-026-02255-7</a></p>This study shows that cerebellar circuits learn and encode prior probabilities of event timing. Cell-type-specific neural activity reflects environmental statistics and guides predictive motor behavior, providing support for neural Bayesian inference.",
